---
import { withBase } from '../utils/paths';
import LegalLayout from '../components/legal/LegalLayout.astro';
import LegalSection from '../components/legal/LegalSection.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Draft Privacy Notice | NozzleNote by BMR"
  description="Preliminary privacy notice placeholder for NozzleNote by BMR, including current static website status and conditional future data categories."
  eyebrow="Draft privacy notice"
  heading="Preliminary privacy notice for future review."
  intro="This draft explains the current privacy direction for the static website and the planned local-first desktop app while NozzleNote by BMR is still in development."
  currentPath="/privacy/"
>
  <LegalSection title="Current status">
    <p>
      NozzleNote by BMR is still in development, and the app is not publicly available yet. This privacy notice is a
      preliminary placeholder intended to guide future review before any public release, payment flow, expanded analytics,
      newsletter, support intake, licensing system, cloud feature, mobile companion, or account system is added.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Current website data collection status">
    <p>
      The current public website is a static Astro site. It conditionally includes the standard GA4 Google tag when
      `PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID` is configured for the build. The repository does not include account registration,
      checkout, newsletter signup, contact forms, authentication, license activation, cloud backup, diagnostic upload,
      custom analytics events, or backend data collection at this stage.
    </p>
    <p>
      Google Analytics, hosting providers, browsers, or network infrastructure may still process basic technical information
      such as IP addresses, request times, user agents, pageview activity, and security logs. A future production
      deployment should document the actual analytics, hosting, and log retention details before launch.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Local-first data direction">
    <p>
      NozzleNote by BMR is designed with a local-first direction for desktop maintenance tracking. The intended product
      direction is that printer profiles, maintenance records, parts notes, incidents, reminders, and related app data are
      primarily managed on the user's own device rather than requiring a hosted account by default.
    </p>
    <p>
      Final technical details, storage behavior, backup options, export behavior, and any optional sync or support flows
      remain subject to implementation and legal review. Users should plan to maintain their own backups when the app is
      eventually released.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Future or conditional data categories">
    <p>
      The following categories are listed for planning only. They are not presented as current website collection, and
      they should not be collected unless the related feature is implemented, documented, and reviewed first.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>License email, if future license activation or purchase recovery is introduced.</li>
      <li>Device hash or similar device identifier, if future device activation is introduced.</li>
      <li>Activation data, entitlements, and license status, if future paid catalogs or license keys are introduced.</li>
      <li>Diagnostic logs, if a future user-controlled diagnostic export or support workflow is implemented.</li>
      <li>Optional account data, if a future account system is added.</li>
      <li>Optional cloud backup data, if a future cloud backup feature is added.</li>
      <li>Future mobile companion data, if a mobile companion workflow is implemented.</li>
      <li>Print quality photos, only if a future photo-based quality history feature is implemented.</li>
    </ul>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="No compliance claim">
    <p>
      This draft does not claim that NozzleNote by BMR satisfies any specific privacy law. Future legal review should
      determine which laws apply, what disclosures are required, and whether additional privacy controls are needed before
      public availability or any data-collecting feature launches.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Future changes">
    <p>
      If future milestones add expanded analytics, crash reporting, support forms, email updates, licensing systems, payment
      processors, cloud features, mobile companion workflows, app distribution platforms, or quality-photo workflows, this
      notice should be updated before those features are launched. Related release status is listed on the
      <a href={withBase('/download/')}>release preparation page</a>, and planned work is summarized on the
      <a href={withBase('/roadmap/')}>roadmap</a>.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Support reference">
    <p>
      Until a final support channel is selected, privacy-related questions should be treated as part of the general
      product readiness work described in the <a href={withBase('/support/')}>support hub</a>. A reviewed contact method should be
      added before public launch.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>
</LegalLayout>
